Preconditions:
- The length of the `cost` array is equal to the length of the `time` array.
- The length of the `cost` array is greater than or equal to 1.
- The values in the `cost` array are positive integers.
- The values in the `time` array are positive integers.
- The maximum value in the `cost` array is less than or equal to 10^6.
- The maximum value in the `time` array is less than or equal to 500.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum amount of money required to paint the walls.
- The returned value is greater than or equal to 0.